<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="359" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,150,321]" pageId="28" pageNumber="359">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,186,212]" pageId="28" pageNumber="359">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This genus is superficially similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Ghauri" authorityName="Ghauri" authorityYear="1962" box="[754,908,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Thaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="359" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[754,819,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="359">Thaia</emphasis>
Ghauri
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kuoh" authorityName="Kuoh" authorityYear="1982" box="[921,1105,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Parathaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="359" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[921,1035,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="359">Parathaia</emphasis>
Kuoh
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Cao &amp; Dmitriev &amp; Dietrich &amp; Zhang, 2020" authorityName="Cao &amp; Dmitriev &amp; Dietrich &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2020" box="[1162,1254,187,212]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Etmaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="359" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[1162,1254,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="359">Etmaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1262,1343,187,213]" pageId="28" pageNumber="359">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1262,1343,187,213]" pageId="28" pageNumber="359" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, but the subgenital plate of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuoh" authorityYear="1982" box="[370,510,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pseudothaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="359" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[370,510,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="359">Pseudothaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very distinctive: the base is fused to sternite IX and the distal disc is flattened as the base and has a thorn-like process apically. Also, the pygofer ventral appendage is quite solid and the style is much longer and has a rudimentary preapical lobe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
